IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. FILE-SPLITTER.
AUTHOR. Simon Mikkelsen.
* This program is a delightful journey into the world of file splitting.
* It takes a file and splits it into smaller files based on user input.
* The program is designed to be a learning experience, filled with
* whimsical variables and functions that add a touch of magic.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'input.txt'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'output.txt'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-RECORD-COUNT PIC 9(5) VALUE 0.
01  WS-FILE-NUMBER PIC 9(3) VALUE 1.
01  WS-USER-INPUT PIC X(10).
01  WS-LOOP-COUNTER PIC 9(5).
01  WS-TEMP-VAR PIC X(100).
01  WS-FILE-NAME PIC X(20).
01  WS-STRING-OF-POWER PIC X(50).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PROCEDURE.
    DISPLAY "Welcome to the File Splitter Program!"
    DISPLAY "Please enter the number of lines per split file:"
    ACCEPT WS-USER-INPUT
    MOVE WS-USER-INPUT TO WS-STRING-OF-POWER
    PERFORM OPEN-FILES
    PERFORM SPLIT-FILE
    PERFORM CLOSE-FILES
    DISPLAY "File splitting is complete. Have a wonderful day!"
    STOP RUN.

OPEN-FILES.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE.

SPLIT-FILE.
    PERFORM UNTIL WS-RECORD-COUNT > 10000
     READ INPUT-FILE INTO WS-TEMP-VAR
     AT END
         EXIT PERFORM
     NOT AT END
         ADD 1 TO WS-RECORD-COUNT
         IF WS-RECORD-COUNT > FUNCTION NUMVAL(WS-STRING-OF-POWER)
          PERFORM CLOSE-OUTPUT-FILE
          ADD 1 TO WS-FILE-NUMBER
          PERFORM OPEN-NEW-OUTPUT-FILE
          MOVE 1 TO WS-RECORD-COUNT
         END-IF
         WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD FROM WS-TEMP-VAR
     END-READ
    END-PERFORM.

CLOSE-FILES.
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE.

CLOSE-OUTPUT-FILE.
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE.